And this is from a section titled

01:08:24.640 --> 01:08:30.000
How do African Americans compare with blacks in Africa on cognitive tests?

01:08:30.000 --> 01:08:31.120
And I quote,

01:08:31.120 --> 01:08:35.520
This question often arises in the context of black-white comparisons in America,

01:08:35.520 --> 01:08:38.160
the thought being that the African black population

01:08:38.160 --> 01:08:40.720
has not been subjected to the historical legacy

01:08:40.720 --> 01:08:43.360
of American black slavery and discrimination

01:08:43.360 --> 01:08:45.760
and might therefore have higher scores.

01:08:45.760 --> 01:08:48.480
Richard Lynn was able to assemble 11 studies

01:08:48.480 --> 01:08:51.040
in his 1991 review of the literature.

01:08:51.040 --> 01:08:55.200
He estimated the median black African IQ to be 75,

01:08:55.200 --> 01:09:00.800
approximately 1.7 standard deviations below the US overall population average,

01:09:00.800 --> 01:09:04.880
about 10 points lower than the current figure for American blacks.

01:09:04.880 --> 01:09:07.440
In summary, African blacks are, on average,

01:09:07.440 --> 01:09:11.280
substantially below African Americans in intelligence test scores.

01:09:11.840 --> 01:09:14.720
Psychometrically, there is little reason to think that these results

01:09:14.720 --> 01:09:17.040
mean anything different about cognitive functioning

01:09:17.040 --> 01:09:19.520
than they mean in non-African populations.

01:09:19.520 --> 01:09:22.240
For our purposes, the main point is that the hypothesis

01:09:22.240 --> 01:09:26.160
about the special circumstances of American blacks depressing their test scores

01:09:26.160 --> 01:09:29.120
is not substantiated by the African data.

01:09:29.120 --> 01:09:31.120
So this is Herrnstein and Murray's answer

01:09:31.120 --> 01:09:35.680
to those who point to the legacy of slavery and discrimination in the United States

01:09:35.680 --> 01:09:38.480
as an explanation for the differences in IQ scores

01:09:38.480 --> 01:09:40.720
between its black and white populations.

01:09:40.720 --> 01:09:42.880
They point to black people in Africa and say,

01:09:42.880 --> 01:09:45.680
hey, well, they also got lower scores.

01:09:45.680 --> 01:09:50.720
Black African people haven't been subject to discrimination in America after all,

01:09:50.720 --> 01:09:54.400
so doesn't this prove that discrimination in America

01:09:54.400 --> 01:09:56.480
can't be depressing black IQ scores?

01:09:57.040 --> 01:09:58.800
Well, not really.

01:09:58.800 --> 01:10:01.760
Herrnstein and Murray's decision to limit their concern here

01:10:01.760 --> 01:10:06.160
to American black slavery and discrimination is a huge oversight

01:10:06.160 --> 01:10:10.080
because there could also be discrimination in whichever parts of Africa

01:10:10.080 --> 01:10:12.160
they are talking about, if you follow.

01:10:12.160 --> 01:10:16.880
That could be, in a similar way, depressing the scores there, too.

01:10:16.880 --> 01:10:19.920
If that were the case, attempting to use the African data

01:10:19.920 --> 01:10:22.640
as some sort of control test for the American data

01:10:22.640 --> 01:10:25.200
would be fairly ridiculous, to say the least.

01:10:25.200 --> 01:10:29.760
America does not have a monopoly on discrimination and depression, does it?

01:10:29.760 --> 01:10:34.080
And so we need to ask, which parts of Africa are they talking about?

01:10:34.080 --> 01:10:38.000
They say that Richard Lin was able to assemble 11 studies

01:10:38.000 --> 01:10:40.800
in his 1991 review of the literature.

01:10:40.800 --> 01:10:43.200
Now, Herrnstein and Murray claiming the acknowledgments

01:10:43.200 --> 01:10:45.600
at the start of the bell curve to have benefited

01:10:45.600 --> 01:10:48.400
especially from the advice of this Richard Lin,

01:10:48.400 --> 01:10:52.720
who they elsewhere call a leading scholar of racial and ethnic differences,

01:10:52.720 --> 01:10:55.920
and they cite his work several times throughout the book.

01:10:55.920 --> 01:11:00.480
So let's take a look at Richard Lin's 1991 review of the literature,

01:11:00.480 --> 01:11:04.800
entitled, Race Differences in Intelligence, A Global Perspective,

01:11:04.800 --> 01:11:07.680
which was published in Mankind Quarterly,

01:11:07.680 --> 01:11:09.920
and remember the name of that journal, folks,

01:11:09.920 --> 01:11:12.400
as we'll be talking more about that later on.

01:11:12.400 --> 01:11:14.640
So the first thing we'll notice about this review

01:11:14.640 --> 01:11:17.360
is that it unfortunately designates people as either

01:11:17.360 --> 01:11:20.640
caucasoids, mongoloids, or negroids,

01:11:20.640 --> 01:11:23.600
including, quote, hybrids of those groups,

01:11:23.600 --> 01:11:27.680
for instance, caucasoid, negroid, hybrids, and so on.

01:11:27.680 --> 01:11:31.120
I can only apologize for having to read out this rubbish.

01:11:31.120 --> 01:11:34.080
So let's look at the 11 studies included in this review

01:11:34.080 --> 01:11:37.360
and see which areas of Africa we are concerned with.

01:11:37.360 --> 01:11:41.200
Well, there's one from what was then known as the Belgian Congo,

01:11:41.200 --> 01:11:44.480
one from Ghana, two from Nigeria, one from Uganda,

01:11:44.480 --> 01:11:48.400
one from Zambia, and five from South Africa.

01:11:48.400 --> 01:11:50.320
And there is rather a lot to comment on here,

01:11:50.320 --> 01:11:53.200
but how about we start with sample sizes?

01:11:53.200 --> 01:11:56.480
Some of them are rather small, you may have noticed.

01:11:56.480 --> 01:12:01.440
87 people for Nigeria, 50 people for Uganda, and so on.

01:12:01.440 --> 01:12:05.040
By far the most represented area here is South Africa.

01:12:05.040 --> 01:12:07.360
The number of people tested in South Africa

01:12:07.360 --> 01:12:11.280
was more than double the number of all the other subjects combined.

01:12:11.280 --> 01:12:13.280
And what's the significance of this?

01:12:13.280 --> 01:12:16.320
Well, this review was published in 1991.

01:12:16.320 --> 01:12:20.080
South African apartheid ended in 1994.

01:12:20.080 --> 01:12:22.800
Now, I don't want to get too deep into this right now,

01:12:22.800 --> 01:12:24.240
but for those who don't know,

01:12:24.240 --> 01:12:27.360
apartheid was an explicitly white supremacist system

01:12:27.360 --> 01:12:29.680
of enforced racial segregation.

01:12:29.680 --> 01:12:32.960
Non-white South Africans were openly discriminated against,

01:12:32.960 --> 01:12:35.840
forced from their homes, forbidden to live in certain areas

01:12:35.840 --> 01:12:38.800
and hold certain jobs, and most importantly for us here,

01:12:38.800 --> 01:12:41.040
had to attend segregated schools,

01:12:41.040 --> 01:12:43.920
which were massively underfunded compared to the schools

01:12:43.920 --> 01:12:46.160
that the white South Africans went to,

01:12:46.160 --> 01:12:50.000
many being without electricity or even running water.

01:12:50.000 --> 01:12:53.440
And just so we know the sort of education system we're dealing with here,

01:12:53.440 --> 01:12:56.480
I'll quickly quote some relevant passages from South Africa,

01:12:56.480 --> 01:12:59.440
a country study from the Library of Congress.

01:12:59.440 --> 01:13:02.400
The Bantu Education Act of 1953

01:13:02.400 --> 01:13:05.120
widened the gaps in educational opportunities

01:13:05.120 --> 01:13:06.800
for different racial groups.

01:13:06.800 --> 01:13:09.280
Two of the architects of Bantu education,

01:13:09.280 --> 01:13:12.960
Dr. W.M. Iselin and Dr. Hendrik F. Ferwerd,

01:13:12.960 --> 01:13:15.920
had studied in Germany and adopted many elements

01:13:15.920 --> 01:13:19.200
of National Socialist, Nazi, philosophy.

01:13:19.760 --> 01:13:22.320
The concept of racial purity in particular

01:13:22.320 --> 01:13:26.560
provided a rationalization for keeping black education inferior.

01:13:26.560 --> 01:13:29.120
Ferwerd, then Minister of Native Affairs,

01:13:29.200 --> 01:13:31.760
said that black Africans should be educated

01:13:31.760 --> 01:13:34.160
for their opportunities in life

01:13:34.160 --> 01:13:35.760
and that there was no place for them

01:13:35.760 --> 01:13:38.720
above the level of certain forms of labor.

01:13:38.720 --> 01:13:40.960
The Bantu Education Act helped pave the way

01:13:40.960 --> 01:13:43.920
for labor strife in the 1980s and 1990s

01:13:43.920 --> 01:13:47.120
by institutionalizing a plan to restrict black workers

01:13:47.120 --> 01:13:50.400
to low-paid jobs through deliberately inferior education.

01:13:51.200 --> 01:13:53.600
During the 1960s and 1970s,

01:13:53.600 --> 01:13:55.360
per capita spending on white pupils

01:13:55.360 --> 01:13:58.240
was about ten times greater than educational spending

01:13:58.240 --> 01:13:59.440
on black pupils.

01:13:59.440 --> 01:14:02.560
By the early 1990s, the gap had been reduced by half,

01:14:02.560 --> 01:14:04.960
but in general, standards for teacher qualifications

01:14:04.960 --> 01:14:06.400
and facilities in black schools

01:14:06.400 --> 01:14:09.520
continued to be inferior to those in white schools.

01:14:09.520 --> 01:14:12.880
The discrepancies in education among racial groups were glaring.

01:14:12.880 --> 01:14:15.120
Teacher-pupil ratios in primary schools

01:14:15.120 --> 01:14:17.360
averaged 1 to 18 in white schools,

01:14:17.360 --> 01:14:19.280
1 to 24 in Asian schools,

01:14:19.280 --> 01:14:21.280
1 to 27 in colored schools,

01:14:21.280 --> 01:14:23.440
and 1 to 39 in black schools.

01:14:24.080 --> 01:14:27.200
Moreover, whereas 96% of all teachers in white schools

01:14:27.200 --> 01:14:28.480
had teaching certificates,

01:14:28.480 --> 01:14:32.160
only 15% of teachers in black schools were certified.

01:14:32.160 --> 01:14:34.240
Secondary school pass rates for black pupils

01:14:34.240 --> 01:14:37.040
in the nationwide standardized high school graduation exams

01:14:37.040 --> 01:14:39.440
were less than one-half the pass rate for whites.

01:14:40.080 --> 01:14:41.360
You get the point, I think.

01:14:41.920 --> 01:14:44.160
So what Hernstein and Murray have done here

01:14:44.160 --> 01:14:47.520
in attempting to prove that a history of racial discrimination

01:14:47.520 --> 01:14:50.880
in America is not depressing black IQ scores

01:14:50.880 --> 01:14:53.520
is point to a study citing similar scores

01:14:53.520 --> 01:14:56.400
in a system of open racial discrimination.

01:14:56.400 --> 01:14:59.200
This is utterly ridiculous, obviously.

01:14:59.200 --> 01:15:01.760
Anyway, we're now gonna take a look at some of these studies

01:15:01.760 --> 01:15:03.440
compiled by Richard Lin,

01:15:03.440 --> 01:15:06.800
and we'll start with this one, Woburn 1969,

01:15:06.800 --> 01:15:11.680
which apparently reported an IQ score of 86 from Nigeria.

01:15:11.680 --> 01:15:14.080
And here it is, the meaning and stability

01:15:14.080 --> 01:15:17.120
of Raven's matrices test among Africans,

01:15:17.120 --> 01:15:18.960
and let's read a little of that.

01:15:18.960 --> 01:15:22.080
This paper aims to clarify our understanding of factors

01:15:22.080 --> 01:15:24.640
affecting African scores on ability tests,

01:15:24.640 --> 01:15:26.800
Raven's matrices in particular.

01:15:26.800 --> 01:15:28.720
Though the main burden is theoretical,

01:15:28.720 --> 01:15:31.280
some fresh data from Nigeria will be shown.

01:15:31.280 --> 01:15:34.320
During 1965, a testing program was carried out

01:15:34.320 --> 01:15:36.320
among factory workers in Nigeria.

01:15:36.320 --> 01:15:39.360
The results from 86 men will be reported here.

01:15:39.360 --> 01:15:41.760
They were tested individually in English or Pidgin

01:15:41.760 --> 01:15:44.880
by the author with the aid of a trained Nigerian assistant.

01:15:44.880 --> 01:15:48.080
Among the test battery were Raven's progressive matrices

01:15:48.080 --> 01:15:50.560
and an adapted embedded figures test,

01:15:50.560 --> 01:15:52.960
which with an index of educational attainment

01:15:52.960 --> 01:15:54.560
are explained by Woburn.

01:15:54.560 --> 01:15:56.000
Six months after the tests,

01:15:56.000 --> 01:15:58.160
each man was given the matrices again.

01:15:58.160 --> 01:15:59.760
There was no intervening coaching,

01:15:59.760 --> 01:16:02.400
and the test was given as though it was to be a new experience

01:16:02.400 --> 01:16:04.000
with full instructions repeated

01:16:04.000 --> 01:16:07.920
and evidently equally necessary in most cases as previously.

01:16:07.920 --> 01:16:10.160
Men were not overtly asked to pit their presence

01:16:10.160 --> 01:16:11.840
against their previous efforts.

01:16:11.840 --> 01:16:14.080
Results were presented in table one.

01:16:14.080 --> 01:16:17.280
The relation between retested matrices and EFT

01:16:17.280 --> 01:16:18.560
is significantly greater

01:16:18.560 --> 01:16:21.760
than between the initial matrices testing and EFT,

01:16:21.760 --> 01:16:23.600
even though in the former comparisons,

01:16:23.600 --> 01:16:26.000
the tests were done six months apart.

01:16:26.000 --> 01:16:28.800
Table one shows that the overall differences in retesting

01:16:28.800 --> 01:16:31.280
were significant and suggests that improvements

01:16:31.280 --> 01:16:34.800
were found particularly among the lower initial scorers.

01:16:34.800 --> 01:16:38.000
Taken with the improved EFT correlation in table two,

01:16:38.000 --> 01:16:40.560
a strong case can be made that the second testing

01:16:40.560 --> 01:16:42.480
gave a distinctly more valid measure

01:16:42.480 --> 01:16:46.160
of whatever abilities the matrices and EFT involve.

01:16:46.160 --> 01:16:48.960
So to quickly summarize, in 1965,

01:16:48.960 --> 01:16:52.000
researchers gave 86 Nigerian factory workers

01:16:52.000 --> 01:16:53.840
the Raven's Progressive Matrices Test

01:16:53.840 --> 01:16:56.160
and then gave it to them again six months later.

01:16:56.160 --> 01:16:57.600
The second time they took the test,

01:16:57.600 --> 01:16:59.040
they performed better overall,

01:16:59.040 --> 01:17:00.640
and the results better correlated

01:17:00.640 --> 01:17:03.200
with another test they took called the EFT.

01:17:03.200 --> 01:17:05.680
And table one here shows both mean results,

01:17:05.680 --> 01:17:10.400
15.9 the first time, increasing to 18.73 the second time.

01:17:10.400 --> 01:17:14.240
What is missing here, you may have noticed, is an IQ score.

01:17:14.240 --> 01:17:16.640
This study does not report an IQ score

01:17:16.640 --> 01:17:18.400
for anyone involved in the test.

01:17:18.400 --> 01:17:20.960
It reports their scores on the matrices test.

01:17:21.520 --> 01:17:25.040
So why then does Lin's review cite Wober 1969

01:17:25.040 --> 01:17:28.080
as having reported an IQ score of 86?

01:17:28.080 --> 01:17:32.400
Well, looking at table one, 86 men took the test.

01:17:33.120 --> 01:17:33.680
Do you see?

01:17:34.480 --> 01:17:38.160
Now, most likely here, this is a simple typographical error,

01:17:38.160 --> 01:17:40.720
and Lin, or whoever typed up his data,

01:17:40.720 --> 01:17:42.880
accidentally wrote the number of test subjects

01:17:42.880 --> 01:17:44.480
in the IQ field.

01:17:44.480 --> 01:17:47.360
Regardless, though, Lin's review is not accurately

01:17:47.360 --> 01:17:50.560
reporting the IQ score from Wober 1969

01:17:50.560 --> 01:17:52.160
because there wasn't one.

01:17:52.160 --> 01:17:55.680
Lin cites Wober 1969 again in his later book,

01:17:55.680 --> 01:17:58.080
IQ and the Wealth of Nations,

01:17:58.080 --> 01:18:01.600
where he says in 1965, norms for the standard

01:18:01.600 --> 01:18:04.960
progressive matrices were collected by Wober 1969

01:18:04.960 --> 01:18:07.280
for a sample of 86 adult men.

01:18:07.280 --> 01:18:09.760
Their mean score was 15.9.

01:18:09.760 --> 01:18:11.600
And then he later claims that this equates

01:18:11.600 --> 01:18:13.680
to an IQ of 64.

01:18:13.680 --> 01:18:16.240
Now, there are several lies by omission here.

01:18:16.240 --> 01:18:21.120
Firstly, Wober 1969 did not report a mean score of 15.9.

01:18:21.120 --> 01:18:23.680
It reported a mean score of 15.9

01:18:23.680 --> 01:18:27.120
and a mean score of 18.73.

01:18:27.120 --> 01:18:29.920
It showed how scores go up with retesting.

01:18:29.920 --> 01:18:32.080
And additionally, it claims that a strong case

01:18:32.080 --> 01:18:34.000
can be made that the second testing

01:18:34.000 --> 01:18:35.840
gave a distinctly more valid measure

01:18:35.840 --> 01:18:39.040
of whatever abilities the matrices and EFT involve.

01:18:39.040 --> 01:18:41.680
Lin intentionally chooses to only report

01:18:41.680 --> 01:18:43.200
the lower score here.

01:18:43.200 --> 01:18:45.840
Another lie by omission here is that Lin declines

01:18:45.840 --> 01:18:48.720
to mention that the sample of 86 adult men

01:18:48.720 --> 01:18:52.400
were not randomly drawn from the general Nigerian population.

01:18:52.400 --> 01:18:54.720
They were not an accurate representation

01:18:54.720 --> 01:18:56.240
of the society where they lived,

01:18:56.240 --> 01:18:58.320
and nor were they intended to be.

01:18:58.320 --> 01:19:00.560
They were all factory workers.

01:19:00.560 --> 01:19:03.760
Reporting the test results of only 86 men

01:19:03.760 --> 01:19:06.080
who are all employed in the same job

01:19:06.080 --> 01:19:07.840
as representative of a country,

01:19:07.840 --> 01:19:11.280
which at the time had a population of 50 million people,

01:19:11.280 --> 01:19:12.880
is... rubbish.

01:19:14.160 --> 01:19:15.040
Just rubbish.

01:19:15.680 --> 01:19:17.680
Next up, let's talk about this result,

01:19:17.680 --> 01:19:21.440
an IQ of 75 for people in Zambia,

01:19:21.440 --> 01:19:27.360
cited from Pons 1974 and Crawford Nutt 1976.

01:19:27.360 --> 01:19:31.280
So the 1976 paper from Crawford Nutt is titled

01:19:31.280 --> 01:19:34.480
Are Black Scores on Raven's Standard Progressive Matrices

01:19:34.480 --> 01:19:36.960
an Artifact of Test Presentation?

01:19:36.960 --> 01:19:40.080
And opens by saying that previous research has shown that

01:19:40.080 --> 01:19:42.400
when the method of test presentation ensures

01:19:42.400 --> 01:19:45.200
that testees understand adequately the requirements

01:19:45.200 --> 01:19:46.880
of the test situation,

01:19:46.880 --> 01:19:49.520
when the method also makes certain that the testees know

01:19:49.520 --> 01:19:52.640
how items of the test are to be responded to,

01:19:52.640 --> 01:19:55.600
and when the method reduces the anxiety of the subjects

01:19:55.600 --> 01:19:57.120
about being tested,

01:19:57.120 --> 01:20:00.160
then the results obtained from the administration of the test

01:20:00.160 --> 01:20:02.560
are remarkably different from those that result

01:20:02.560 --> 01:20:05.280
from administration in which the same test is presented

01:20:05.280 --> 01:20:07.200
in the same way to all testees,

01:20:07.200 --> 01:20:09.440
regardless of their cultural origin.

01:20:09.440 --> 01:20:12.480
It goes on to detail how a researcher named Pons

01:20:12.480 --> 01:20:15.200
gave the Raven's Standard Progressive Matrices test

01:20:15.200 --> 01:20:18.800
to a group of Zambian copper miners in 1962,

01:20:18.800 --> 01:20:21.040
using the standard method of delivery.

01:20:21.600 --> 01:20:25.040
Then later, Pons administered the test again to another group,

01:20:25.040 --> 01:20:28.800
only this time using a different method of test presentation.

01:20:28.800 --> 01:20:30.240
As table one shows,

01:20:30.240 --> 01:20:34.000
the second group showed a rather dramatic difference in score.

01:20:34.000 --> 01:20:36.080
Now, the thinking behind all this might be

01:20:36.080 --> 01:20:38.400
that a group of Zambian copper miners

01:20:38.400 --> 01:20:40.800
aren't necessarily going to be all that familiar

01:20:40.800 --> 01:20:43.680
with taking academic tests, not to generalize,

01:20:43.680 --> 01:20:45.600
and if you want more accurate results,

01:20:45.600 --> 01:20:48.880
it might be worth taking the time to actually explain to them

01:20:48.880 --> 01:20:51.120
what it is that they're being expected to do.

01:20:51.680 --> 01:20:52.960
Now, Crawford Knott claims

01:20:52.960 --> 01:20:54.720
that the different method of presentation

01:20:54.720 --> 01:20:57.040
did not alter anything about the test itself

01:20:57.040 --> 01:21:00.240
and is based upon suggestions found in the 1960 guide

01:21:00.240 --> 01:21:04.160
to the standard progressive matrices written by John C. Raven,

01:21:04.160 --> 01:21:08.640
AKA the guy what invented the Raven's Progressive Matrices test.

01:21:08.640 --> 01:21:10.880
After reporting the findings of Pons,

01:21:10.880 --> 01:21:13.360
Crawford Knott takes things one step further

01:21:13.360 --> 01:21:17.200
and tests a selection of pupils from a long-established high school

01:21:17.200 --> 01:21:22.080
situated in the black residential area of Soweto near Johannesburg,

01:21:22.080 --> 01:21:24.720
a school that is described as having high standards

01:21:24.720 --> 01:21:27.680
and whose students would be used to being tested.

01:21:27.680 --> 01:21:30.640
Crawford Knott tested two samples of these schoolchildren

01:21:30.640 --> 01:21:33.680
using the same presentation method as described by Pons,

01:21:33.680 --> 01:21:36.400
and the results received were actually slightly higher

01:21:36.400 --> 01:21:39.280
than the equivalent age range of the white group

01:21:39.280 --> 01:21:41.600
on whom the test was normalized.

01:21:41.600 --> 01:21:45.680
Now, you might say, what has Crawford Knott actually proved there?

01:21:45.680 --> 01:21:50.320
Test results go up the closer you get to a good school, I suppose.

01:21:50.320 --> 01:21:52.640
This shouldn't be surprising anyone.

01:21:52.640 --> 01:21:56.080
If you test a relatively uneducated group of copper miners,

01:21:56.080 --> 01:21:57.440
you get one result.

01:21:57.440 --> 01:22:00.800
Do that same test in a competitive academic institution

01:22:00.800 --> 01:22:02.720
and you will get a higher result.

01:22:02.720 --> 01:22:04.960
By changing the method of test presentation

01:22:04.960 --> 01:22:07.520
and changing the group which you are testing,

01:22:07.520 --> 01:22:09.600
you can get a whole range of results.

01:22:09.600 --> 01:22:12.320
This is why researchers don't usually test people

01:22:12.320 --> 01:22:15.600
in just one area, one workplace, or one school

01:22:15.600 --> 01:22:18.080
and then try to pass off that singular result

01:22:18.080 --> 01:22:21.600
as representative of the entire country that they live in.

01:22:21.600 --> 01:22:24.560
That would be a remarkably ignorant thing to do.

01:22:25.280 --> 01:22:30.240
Speaking of, back to Richard Lin and his claimed IQ of 75 for Zambia,

01:22:30.240 --> 01:22:32.800
which cites both Pons and Crawford Knott

01:22:32.800 --> 01:22:34.480
as the source of the data there.

01:22:34.480 --> 01:22:36.240
So how did that happen?

01:22:36.240 --> 01:22:39.760
Well, what Lin does is, he cites the much lower results

01:22:39.760 --> 01:22:41.760
from the research carried out by Pons,

01:22:41.760 --> 01:22:44.720
which are presented in Crawford Knott's paper,

01:22:44.720 --> 01:22:48.240
and then completely ignores Crawford Knott's experiment in the school,

01:22:48.240 --> 01:22:50.960
which reported results above the white norm.

01:22:51.600 --> 01:22:55.840
The entire point of Crawford Knott's paper goes totally unmentioned by Lin,

01:22:55.840 --> 01:23:00.240
who simply extracts the data that he wants and discards the rest.

01:23:00.240 --> 01:23:03.360
He had data showing a black African test score

01:23:03.360 --> 01:23:05.120
that was above the white norm,

01:23:05.120 --> 01:23:08.000
and he simply decided to ignore it.

01:23:08.000 --> 01:23:10.320
Also, like the previous paper we discussed,

01:23:10.320 --> 01:23:14.560
this study did not report IQ scores for the testees.

01:23:14.560 --> 01:23:16.400
Those are simply concocted by Lin

01:23:16.400 --> 01:23:18.880
out of the Raven's progressive matrices data,

01:23:18.880 --> 01:23:23.120
using a sophisticated statistical technique called guessing.

01:23:23.120 --> 01:23:24.960
So to understand what Lin has done here,

01:23:24.960 --> 01:23:29.200
we need to talk a little about IQ test construction and standardization.

01:23:29.200 --> 01:23:31.200
And let's start with the bell curve.

01:23:31.840 --> 01:23:35.520
Not the book this time, but the statistical distribution.

01:23:35.520 --> 01:23:41.040
Now, IQ tests, as we know, return this bell curve, or normal distribution.

01:23:41.040 --> 01:23:44.800
This means that the majority of the scores are clustered around the middle

01:23:44.800 --> 01:23:48.560
and taper off towards the ends of the curve in a symmetrical way.

01:23:49.120 --> 01:23:53.280
But why, you might ask, do they actually return this distribution?

01:23:53.280 --> 01:23:55.520
Well, it's because that's how they're designed.

01:23:56.080 --> 01:24:00.800
Psychometricians design IQ tests so that their results match the bell curve.

01:24:00.800 --> 01:24:03.040
If the test they design is too easy,

01:24:03.040 --> 01:24:04.880
then the bell curve will lean to the right,

01:24:04.880 --> 01:24:07.120
as too many people will get high scores.

01:24:07.680 --> 01:24:10.240
If the test is too hard, it will lean to the left,

01:24:10.240 --> 01:24:12.480
as too many people get low scores.

01:24:12.480 --> 01:24:16.400
And if the test doesn't differentiate between people to the right degree,

01:24:16.400 --> 01:24:19.840
then too many people could be at either end of the curve.

01:24:19.840 --> 01:24:23.520
So the test designers tinker with the difficulty of the test

01:24:23.520 --> 01:24:25.840
until the results match the bell curve.

01:24:26.400 --> 01:24:28.960
So why do psychometricians do this?

01:24:28.960 --> 01:24:32.240
Well, it's because that's how they assume intelligence is distributed

01:24:32.240 --> 01:24:34.000
throughout the human population.

01:24:34.640 --> 01:24:36.880
Emphasis on assume here,

01:24:36.880 --> 01:24:40.400
because we do not actually know how intelligence is distributed

01:24:40.400 --> 01:24:42.160
throughout the human population.

01:24:42.160 --> 01:24:44.800
Unless you specifically design for it,

01:24:44.800 --> 01:24:48.720
tests do not necessarily return a bell curve distribution.

01:24:48.720 --> 01:24:49.840
For example here,

01:24:49.840 --> 01:24:53.280
the armed forces qualifying test used in the bell curve

01:24:53.280 --> 01:24:55.840
did not return a bell curve distribution.

01:24:55.840 --> 01:25:01.200
It was, after all, designed to test readiness to join the armed forces, not IQ.

01:25:01.200 --> 01:25:05.040
As a result, it does not differentiate between people to a large enough degree,

01:25:05.040 --> 01:25:09.120
so Hernstein and Murray, to make the results conform to a bell curve,

01:25:09.120 --> 01:25:11.280
recalculated the scores.

01:25:11.360 --> 01:25:16.080
Here is a graph of the raw AFQT scores overlaid with Hernstein and Murray's

01:25:16.080 --> 01:25:20.400
recalculated bell curve scores from the book Inequality by Design.

01:25:20.400 --> 01:25:23.920
And as we can see, too many people scored too highly on the test

01:25:23.920 --> 01:25:26.400
and there isn't enough differentiation between people

01:25:26.400 --> 01:25:28.800
on the upper end of the scale in particular.

01:25:28.800 --> 01:25:30.160
So yes, that's right.

01:25:30.160 --> 01:25:31.840
In the book The Bell Curve,

01:25:31.840 --> 01:25:35.120
the principal intelligence test the authors use as a source

01:25:35.120 --> 01:25:37.600
did not return a bell curve distribution.

01:25:37.600 --> 01:25:40.240
To transform these results into a bell curve,

01:25:40.240 --> 01:25:44.800
Hernstein and Murray exaggerated the slight differences at the end of the scale.

01:25:44.800 --> 01:25:48.880
They basically gave extra credit for being near the tails of the bell curve

01:25:48.880 --> 01:25:51.120
and less for being in the middle.

01:25:51.120 --> 01:25:55.600
They did this as they explain in Appendix 2 to correct for skew.

01:25:55.600 --> 01:25:58.880
But remember, in relation to how intelligence is distributed

01:25:58.880 --> 01:26:00.720
throughout the human population,

01:26:00.720 --> 01:26:03.120
these results are only actually skewed

01:26:03.120 --> 01:26:07.760
if we assume that intelligence is distributed in a bell curve to begin with.

01:26:07.760 --> 01:26:09.520
This is circular logic.

01:26:09.520 --> 01:26:12.880
We are assuming the result that we are going to get beforehand

01:26:12.880 --> 01:26:16.480
and then designing the test or just manipulating the data

01:26:16.480 --> 01:26:18.560
in order to reach that conclusion.

01:26:18.560 --> 01:26:20.400
Anyway, to get back on track here,

01:26:20.400 --> 01:26:25.120
what does all this have to do with Richard Lin and the Raven's progressive matrices test?

01:26:25.120 --> 01:26:29.280
Well, that test also does not return a bell curve distribution.

01:26:29.280 --> 01:26:32.640
The results are not symmetrically distributed around their mean,

01:26:32.640 --> 01:26:35.600
to quote an article by psychologist Leon Kamin.

01:26:35.600 --> 01:26:39.200
That article also notes that the test's developer, John Raven,

01:26:39.200 --> 01:26:44.480
always insisted that the progressive matrices scores cannot be converted into IQs.

01:26:44.480 --> 01:26:47.760
Here is an example of the distribution of matrix test scores

01:26:47.760 --> 01:26:52.240
from Raven's paper, Standardization of Progressive Matrices 1938.

01:26:52.240 --> 01:26:56.240
And as you can see, those are some very wobbly bell curves right there.

01:26:56.240 --> 01:27:01.120
What the test does give is raw scores which correspond to percentile scores.

01:27:01.120 --> 01:27:05.120
So you can know from your raw score how you compare percentile-wise

01:27:05.120 --> 01:27:07.680
to the group on which the test was normalized.

01:27:07.760 --> 01:27:13.040
But these percentiles will not be distributed evenly around their mean in a bell curve.

01:27:13.040 --> 01:27:17.680
To calculate IQ, Richard Lin takes the average of these raw scores,

01:27:17.680 --> 01:27:20.000
converts them to a percentile score,

01:27:20.000 --> 01:27:24.720
and then gives what the IQ of that percentile score would correspond to

01:27:24.720 --> 01:27:28.240
if the results were in a bell curve distribution.

01:27:28.240 --> 01:27:32.560
Basically, Lin is assuming a bell curve exists where there demonstrably isn't one

01:27:32.560 --> 01:27:34.800
and is forcing the data to fit it.

01:27:34.800 --> 01:27:38.480
Another issue here is that in the decades since the Second World War,

01:27:38.480 --> 01:27:43.760
scores on the Raven's matrices test similar to IQ test scores had been changing.

01:27:43.760 --> 01:27:47.200
Accordingly, the test had been standardized several times.

01:27:47.200 --> 01:27:51.200
So when we're comparing the African results with Western norms,

01:27:51.200 --> 01:27:54.080
we need to identify what norm group we're using

01:27:54.080 --> 01:27:59.280
because comparisons with different groups from different times could give different results.

01:27:59.280 --> 01:28:04.000
Particularly sharp-eyed viewers would have noticed that Lin does exactly this

01:28:04.000 --> 01:28:06.320
in the quote from his 2002 book,

01:28:06.320 --> 01:28:09.200
IQ and the Wealth of Nations, which I showed earlier,

01:28:09.200 --> 01:28:12.160
where he discusses Nigerian IQs, quote,

01:28:12.160 --> 01:28:16.000
in terms of the British 1979 standardization.

01:28:16.560 --> 01:28:19.600
Identifying this standardization is important,

01:28:19.600 --> 01:28:25.040
as using a different one could lead to a different Nigerian IQ being calculated.

01:28:25.040 --> 01:28:29.520
In his 1991 review of the literature cited in the bell curve, however,

01:28:29.520 --> 01:28:35.440
Lin does not identify what standardization he's using for the various tests he is comparing.

01:28:35.440 --> 01:28:38.640
What this means is that there is a gap in Lin's calculations

01:28:38.640 --> 01:28:42.480
that can only be filled by faith in his academic honesty,

01:28:42.480 --> 01:28:44.720
which Hearnstein and Murray clearly have,

01:28:44.720 --> 01:28:47.520
but I must confess that I do not.

01:28:47.520 --> 01:28:51.040
Anyway, if you think what Lin did to those last two studies was bad,

01:28:51.040 --> 01:28:54.240
strap in, because this next one is a real bastard.

01:28:54.240 --> 01:28:59.600
South Africa IQ of 69, attributed to Owen, 1989,

01:28:59.600 --> 01:29:04.240
which Lin calls the single best study of the Negroid Intelligence.

01:29:05.520 --> 01:29:07.520
So this is test and item bias,

01:29:07.520 --> 01:29:11.520
the suitability of the junior aptitude tests as a common test battery

01:29:11.520 --> 01:29:14.560
for white, Indian, and black pupils in standard 7.

01:29:14.560 --> 01:29:17.600
Owen is not one for catchy names, apparently.

01:29:17.600 --> 01:29:20.000
The abstract to this study starts out,

01:29:20.000 --> 01:29:22.560
This study was undertaken to shed light on problems

01:29:22.560 --> 01:29:25.360
concerning the construction and use of a common test battery

01:29:25.360 --> 01:29:27.920
for various South African population groups.

01:29:27.920 --> 01:29:30.480
You see, this study is testing a test,

01:29:30.480 --> 01:29:33.600
the Junior Aptitude Test, or JAT,

01:29:33.600 --> 01:29:36.880
which was standardized for white pupils in South Africa

01:29:36.880 --> 01:29:40.800
and determining whether it's also a good test to give to non-white groups.

01:29:40.800 --> 01:29:46.000
The study selected various schools in South Africa for white, Indian, and black students.

01:29:46.000 --> 01:29:47.120
Although it should be mentioned,

01:29:47.200 --> 01:29:50.480
it was not able to use the majority of the selected black schools,

01:29:50.480 --> 01:29:50.960
quote,

01:29:50.960 --> 01:29:56.640
and thus they had to test black schools in the KwaZulu region,

01:29:56.640 --> 01:30:01.840
one of the areas designated for black inhabitants of South Africa under apartheid.

01:30:01.840 --> 01:30:04.800
I mention the unrest situation here as a reminder that,

01:30:04.800 --> 01:30:07.840
yes, these tests are being carried out under apartheid,

01:30:07.840 --> 01:30:13.040
and protests and demonstrations against the segregated school system were ongoing.

01:30:13.040 --> 01:30:15.600
So anyway, the study examined pupils' performances

01:30:15.600 --> 01:30:18.640
on the various sub-tests comprising the JAT,

01:30:18.640 --> 01:30:20.160
and what were the findings?

01:30:20.160 --> 01:30:22.160
Well, the thing I think we should mention first here

01:30:22.160 --> 01:30:26.480
is that the tests were given to the black students in KwaZulu in English only,

01:30:26.480 --> 01:30:31.600
and several test sections of the JAT relied very heavily upon language ability.

01:30:31.600 --> 01:30:35.120
Now, Owen expected language ability not to matter in the tests

01:30:35.120 --> 01:30:37.760
because the black students in the KwaZulu region

01:30:37.760 --> 01:30:41.120
had ostensibly been learning English in their schools.

01:30:41.120 --> 01:30:43.760
Owen apparently either doesn't know or disregards

01:30:43.760 --> 01:30:47.120
that these schools often didn't have necessary teaching equipment,

01:30:47.120 --> 01:30:49.760
only a small amount of their teachers were certified,

01:30:49.760 --> 01:30:53.440
and that pupil-teacher ratios were more than double that of the white schools.

01:30:53.440 --> 01:30:54.720
And to quote the study,

01:30:54.720 --> 01:30:59.920
language was not expected to play a significant role in test performance in this investigation.

01:30:59.920 --> 01:31:03.760
However, the results showed that this assumption was completely wrong.

01:31:03.760 --> 01:31:06.480
In fact, language played such an important role,

01:31:06.480 --> 01:31:10.080
and the knowledge of English of the majority of black testees was so poor

01:31:10.080 --> 01:31:13.760
that certain tests, for example the JAT-4 synonyms

01:31:13.760 --> 01:31:18.640
and the JAT-8 memory paragraph, proved to be virtually unusable.

01:31:19.360 --> 01:31:21.200
And let me just quote that again.

01:31:21.200 --> 01:31:24.960
Certain tests proved to be virtually unusable.

01:31:24.960 --> 01:31:26.800
Owen also writes elsewhere,

01:31:26.800 --> 01:31:31.520
the results of the current investigation clearly show that language played a prominent role

01:31:31.520 --> 01:31:34.160
in all the tests containing language items,

01:31:34.160 --> 01:31:38.640
which is a wonderful multiple stab wounds shown to shorten life expectancy,

01:31:38.640 --> 01:31:41.280
bit of academic obviousness there.

01:31:41.280 --> 01:31:46.400
Language ability was not the only way in which the Junior Aptitude Test was biased, however.

01:31:46.400 --> 01:31:49.840
In a section entitled Item Bias in the Tests of the JAT,

01:31:49.840 --> 01:31:54.880
Owen notes several ways in which the tests were culturally and economically biased.

01:31:54.880 --> 01:32:00.320
For example, he here lists several test items on the first test in the JAT and states,

01:32:00.320 --> 01:32:04.560
A common element in most of these items was that they presuppose knowledge

01:32:04.560 --> 01:32:07.440
or a degree of knowledge on the part of the testee,

01:32:07.440 --> 01:32:10.480
and mentions such things as electrical appliances,

01:32:10.480 --> 01:32:14.400
microscopes, and Western types of ladies' accessories.

01:32:14.400 --> 01:32:15.680
Going on to write,

01:32:15.680 --> 01:32:18.560
Thus in the case of both the Indian and Black testees,

01:32:18.560 --> 01:32:22.400
it seems that the single largest cause of bias lay in the fact that the pupils

01:32:22.400 --> 01:32:26.240
were not familiar with the objects represented by the pictures.

01:32:26.240 --> 01:32:31.440
Cultural and socioeconomic status factors probably also played a role in this regard.

01:32:31.440 --> 01:32:33.600
So this test is biased, then.

01:32:33.600 --> 01:32:36.800
The study examining it says it is biased,

01:32:36.800 --> 01:32:38.480
but according to Richard Lin,

01:32:38.480 --> 01:32:42.960
this is the single best study of the Negroid Intelligence.

01:32:42.960 --> 01:32:44.480
This is the best one.

01:32:44.480 --> 01:32:48.800
The one that tests segregated school children in a non-native language

01:32:48.800 --> 01:32:51.760
and calls its own results virtually unusable.

01:32:51.760 --> 01:32:52.800
In Lin's review,

01:32:52.800 --> 01:32:56.720
this is the most important study for his estimates of Black African IQ.

01:32:57.280 --> 01:32:58.800
Writing about it, he says,

01:32:58.800 --> 01:33:04.320
The mean IQ of the sample in comparison with Caucasoid South African norms is 69.

01:33:04.320 --> 01:33:08.160
It is also around the median of the studies listed in Table 3.

01:33:08.160 --> 01:33:11.360
It is proposed, therefore, to round this figure up to 70.

01:33:12.400 --> 01:33:13.120
Why?

01:33:13.120 --> 01:33:17.280
And take this as the approximate mean for pure Negroids.

01:33:17.280 --> 01:33:18.320
God damn.

01:33:18.320 --> 01:33:20.800
What Lin has done here is ridiculous.

01:33:20.800 --> 01:33:26.560
He has taken 11 studies from a period between 1929 and 1991,

01:33:26.560 --> 01:33:31.360
with vastly different sample sizes reporting data from different tests,

01:33:31.360 --> 01:33:34.480
most of which didn't even report IQ scores,

01:33:34.480 --> 01:33:39.040
transformed the data into what he reckons the equivalent IQ scores were

01:33:39.040 --> 01:33:41.600
using some unknown standardization,

01:33:41.600 --> 01:33:44.240
picked one that was sort of near the middle,

01:33:44.240 --> 01:33:46.960
and said that's the average Black African IQ.

01:33:47.600 --> 01:33:49.920
This is outrageous.

01:33:49.920 --> 01:33:51.440
It is a crime.

01:33:51.440 --> 01:33:54.720
It might actually be a crime, and if it's not, it should be.

01:33:54.720 --> 01:33:57.600
Now, I am far from the first person to criticize

01:33:57.600 --> 01:34:00.480
the Bell Curve's reliance upon Richard Lin as a source.

01:34:00.960 --> 01:34:04.960
Various academics were already well aware of Lin and his dodgy data,

01:34:04.960 --> 01:34:07.040
so when Herrnstein and Murray cited him,

01:34:07.040 --> 01:34:11.840
they were immediately attacked with accusations of bias and racism.

01:34:11.840 --> 01:34:15.840
Charles Murray responds to these attacks in the afterword to the Bell Curve,

01:34:15.840 --> 01:34:17.520
and his defense is laughable.

01:34:17.520 --> 01:34:20.800
His first defense is to say that the topic of African IQ

01:34:20.800 --> 01:34:26.080
is a tiny piece of the Bell Curve, three paragraphs on pages 288 to 89,

01:34:26.080 --> 01:34:29.520
and in regards to this, two responses jump to mind immediately.

01:34:29.600 --> 01:34:34.160
The first is to say, well, maybe you should have spent longer on it then, Charles.

01:34:34.160 --> 01:34:36.000
We were wrong very quickly.

01:34:36.000 --> 01:34:38.640
Isn't a defense against being wrong, is it?

01:34:38.640 --> 01:34:40.400
Maybe if you put a little more effort in,

01:34:40.400 --> 01:34:43.520
you would have seen that Lin's paper was a load of rubbish.

01:34:43.520 --> 01:34:48.160
Secondly, this part of the Bell Curve is far more important than Murray makes out.

01:34:48.160 --> 01:34:51.200
He uses Lin's paper to dismiss the arguments

01:34:51.200 --> 01:34:55.360
that black-white differences in IQ are caused by environmental factors,

01:34:55.360 --> 01:34:57.120
such as a history of oppression,

01:34:57.120 --> 01:34:59.920
which is the single most common counterargument

01:34:59.920 --> 01:35:02.880
to one of the principal claims in the entire book.

01:35:02.880 --> 01:35:07.440
At no point does Murray actually address any specific criticisms of Lin's work

01:35:07.440 --> 01:35:09.520
or any of its various errors.

01:35:09.520 --> 01:35:14.560
He mainly just seems outraged that anyone dares to have criticized him at all, to be honest.

01:35:14.560 --> 01:35:17.280
And it's exactly this sort of academic laziness

01:35:17.280 --> 01:35:20.480
that fed much of the angry response to the Bell Curve.

01:35:20.480 --> 01:35:23.600
Murray refuses to admit that citing Lin was a mistake,

01:35:23.600 --> 01:35:28.720
and simply throws out some newer studies that supposedly show he was right anyway.

01:35:28.720 --> 01:35:29.760
So there.

01:35:29.760 --> 01:35:32.000
This speaks to a couple of things.

01:35:32.000 --> 01:35:36.320
Firstly, it is a fatal underestimation of exactly how badly this damages

01:35:36.320 --> 01:35:40.000
the faith that a reader of the Bell Curve can have in its authors.

01:35:40.000 --> 01:35:43.120
After all, this is not the only time they cite Richard Lin.

01:35:43.120 --> 01:35:46.240
He has more than 20 citations in their bibliography,

01:35:46.240 --> 01:35:49.040
and they thank him specifically in the acknowledgments.

01:35:49.040 --> 01:35:53.520
If this is the sort of data that Charles Murray is willing to accept as legitimate,

01:35:53.520 --> 01:35:56.800
how can we trust anything he says anywhere in the book?

01:35:56.800 --> 01:36:00.320
How can we trust the new studies he brings up to defend Richard Lin?

01:36:00.960 --> 01:36:05.920
Personally, I think it would be a mistake to even look at these new studies.

01:36:05.920 --> 01:36:09.360
Murray's response to having his previous sources called into question

01:36:09.360 --> 01:36:11.760
is to simply throw out new sources.

01:36:11.760 --> 01:36:16.400
His response to having these called into question would no doubt be to throw out more.

01:36:16.400 --> 01:36:20.560
The responsibility for checking whether his sources are trustworthy or accurate

01:36:20.560 --> 01:36:23.760
has been moved from Murray to his critics.

01:36:23.760 --> 01:36:26.160
They're the ones doing the reading and the fact-checking,

01:36:26.160 --> 01:36:28.800
whereas he never gets held to account.

01:36:28.800 --> 01:36:34.000
So long as we all understand that, however, I suppose we can take a brief peek.

01:36:34.000 --> 01:36:35.200
So, Murray says,

01:36:35.200 --> 01:36:40.880
Let me turn to two studies post-dating Richard Lin's review that we cite on page 289.

01:36:40.880 --> 01:36:43.600
One was a South African study led by Kenneth Owen,

01:36:43.600 --> 01:36:48.320
published in the refereed British journal Personality and Individual Differences.

01:36:48.320 --> 01:36:52.320
So this was the suitability of Raven's standard progressive matrices

01:36:52.320 --> 01:36:54.480
for various groups in South Africa,

