their proposals sometimes actually directly contradict with their previous analysis.

02:08:49.600 --> 02:08:52.800
For example, let's talk about affirmative action.

02:08:52.800 --> 02:08:57.520
As mentioned earlier, Hernstein and Murray really don't like affirmative action.

02:08:57.520 --> 02:09:00.000
And as we've also seen, they are very worried

02:09:00.000 --> 02:09:03.920
about the supposed cognitive stratification of society.

02:09:03.920 --> 02:09:06.320
And let's briefly quote them talking about that.

02:09:06.320 --> 02:09:09.440
In this penultimate chapter, we speculate about the impact

02:09:09.440 --> 02:09:13.120
of cognitive stratification on American life and government.

02:09:13.120 --> 02:09:15.920
Predicting the course of society is chancy,

02:09:15.920 --> 02:09:19.280
but certain tendencies seem strong enough to worry about.

02:09:19.280 --> 02:09:22.160
An increasingly isolated cognitive elite,

02:09:22.160 --> 02:09:24.960
a merging of the cognitive elite with the affluent,

02:09:24.960 --> 02:09:27.680
a deteriorating quality of life for people

02:09:27.680 --> 02:09:30.960
at the bottom end of the cognitive ability distribution.

02:09:30.960 --> 02:09:35.760
Unchecked, these trends will lead the US towards something resembling a caste society

02:09:35.760 --> 02:09:38.560
with the underclass mired ever more firmly at the bottom

02:09:38.560 --> 02:09:41.840
and the cognitive elite ever more firmly anchored at the top,

02:09:41.840 --> 02:09:43.920
restructuring the rules of society

02:09:43.920 --> 02:09:47.040
so that it becomes harder and harder for them to lose.

02:09:47.680 --> 02:09:49.760
Among the other casualties of this process

02:09:49.760 --> 02:09:53.360
would be American civil society as we have known it.

02:09:53.360 --> 02:09:58.720
Like other apocalyptic visions, this one is pessimistic, perhaps too much so.

02:09:58.720 --> 02:10:01.680
On the other hand, there is much to be pessimistic about.

02:10:02.240 --> 02:10:04.960
Now what Hernstein and Murray fail to spot here

02:10:04.960 --> 02:10:07.920
is that a policy of aggressive affirmative action

02:10:07.920 --> 02:10:11.360
would directly work to check the cognitive partitioning

02:10:11.360 --> 02:10:13.760
that they call frightening and apocalyptic.

02:10:14.320 --> 02:10:16.480
If Harvard or some other fancy school

02:10:16.480 --> 02:10:19.680
decided they were gonna admit a certain percentage of applicants

02:10:19.680 --> 02:10:23.360
based upon some characteristic other than test scores,

02:10:23.360 --> 02:10:26.800
then there would be that same number of applicants with higher test scores

02:10:26.800 --> 02:10:29.040
who would therefore not get into Harvard

02:10:29.040 --> 02:10:31.920
and have to go to their next choice of college.

02:10:31.920 --> 02:10:35.200
And the next smartest people who would have gone to that college

02:10:35.200 --> 02:10:38.240
will now not get in and have to go to their next choice

02:10:38.240 --> 02:10:40.080
and so on down the line.

02:10:40.080 --> 02:10:42.560
And if this ruthless affirmative action policy

02:10:42.640 --> 02:10:45.280
was adopted by the group of colleges as a whole,

02:10:45.280 --> 02:10:47.680
the cognitive elite would be forced to spread out

02:10:47.680 --> 02:10:49.520
throughout the whole college pool,

02:10:49.520 --> 02:10:53.920
which would have the added effect of spreading them out geographically too.

02:10:53.920 --> 02:10:56.640
Hernstein and Murray really should have spotted this,

02:10:56.640 --> 02:10:59.040
since earlier in the book they talk fondly

02:10:59.040 --> 02:11:02.240
about Harvard's policy of admitting legacy applicants,

02:11:02.240 --> 02:11:06.080
those usually being people whose fathers had graduated from Harvard.

02:11:06.640 --> 02:11:09.520
They also mention applicants being considered for things like

02:11:09.520 --> 02:11:13.840
his potential as a quarterback or stroke for the eight-man shell

02:11:13.840 --> 02:11:16.640
and other non-academic qualities.

02:11:16.640 --> 02:11:19.920
Curiously, Hernstein and Murray do not criticize

02:11:19.920 --> 02:11:24.080
Harvard's practice of admitting people for non-academic reasons.

02:11:24.080 --> 02:11:26.560
When it comes to affirmative action, however,

02:11:26.560 --> 02:11:30.640
Hernstein and Murray are very clear about that being unfair,

02:11:30.640 --> 02:11:31.520
and I quote,

02:11:31.520 --> 02:11:34.000
"...to what extent is a society fair

02:11:34.000 --> 02:11:36.400
when people of similar ability and background

02:11:36.400 --> 02:11:38.800
are treated as differently as they are now?"

02:11:38.800 --> 02:11:42.640
In 1964, the answer would have been unambiguous.

02:11:42.640 --> 02:11:45.680
Such a society is manifestly unfair.

02:11:45.680 --> 02:11:48.560
The logic was right then, and right now.

02:11:48.560 --> 02:11:52.080
So colleges admitting applicants for non-academic reasons,

02:11:52.080 --> 02:11:55.120
such as their father having gone there, that's okay.

02:11:55.120 --> 02:11:59.760
It's counteracting the dreaded cognitive partitioning of society, after all.

02:11:59.760 --> 02:12:03.200
But colleges admitting applicants because of affirmative action,

02:12:03.200 --> 02:12:05.440
well that is, rather dramatically,

02:12:05.440 --> 02:12:08.320
leaking a poison into the American soul.

02:12:08.880 --> 02:12:11.680
So how do we account for this apparent contradiction

02:12:11.680 --> 02:12:13.920
on behalf of Hernstein and Murray?

02:12:13.920 --> 02:12:17.360
Well, what would you imagine to be the most likely difference

02:12:17.360 --> 02:12:22.480
between a legacy Harvard applicant and an affirmative action applicant?

02:12:23.120 --> 02:12:26.000
I will leave it to you to ponder that one.

02:12:26.000 --> 02:12:30.320
Instead of the unfair and poisonous racial affirmative action,

02:12:30.320 --> 02:12:34.960
Hernstein and Murray argue instead for a race-blind version of affirmative action

02:12:34.960 --> 02:12:38.480
based, bizarrely, on test scores.

02:12:38.480 --> 02:12:42.720
And I say bizarrely here because this idea would actually accelerate

02:12:42.720 --> 02:12:46.160
the supposedly apocalyptic cognitive partitioning.

02:12:46.960 --> 02:12:49.040
They say that in the case of two candidates

02:12:49.040 --> 02:12:51.040
who are fairly closely matched otherwise,

02:12:51.040 --> 02:12:55.520
universities should give the nod to the applicant from the disadvantaged background.

02:12:55.520 --> 02:12:58.160
Now, I agree with this in isolation here.

02:12:58.160 --> 02:13:00.880
I do think that if you have two similar candidates,

02:13:00.880 --> 02:13:03.120
you should admit the less privileged one.

02:13:03.120 --> 02:13:07.600
But with regards to Hernstein and Murray's fears of cognitive partitioning, though,

02:13:07.600 --> 02:13:10.320
this is exactly what they were worried about.

02:13:10.320 --> 02:13:15.120
College is becoming better at collecting all of society's high IQ people together

02:13:15.120 --> 02:13:19.520
and funneling them into high IQ jobs in high IQ areas.

02:13:19.520 --> 02:13:20.720
They've basically said,

02:13:20.720 --> 02:13:25.680
here's an apocalyptic problem and now here's how to make it happen faster.

02:13:26.240 --> 02:13:29.360
And actually, regarding the concept of affirmative action,

02:13:29.360 --> 02:13:31.840
their logic is all wrong there.

02:13:31.840 --> 02:13:36.320
At the start of the chapter titled Affirmative Action in Higher Education,

02:13:36.320 --> 02:13:41.200
Hernstein and Murray recount an affirmative action controversy from 1991

02:13:41.200 --> 02:13:44.320
where a law student at Georgetown University, quote,

02:13:44.320 --> 02:13:47.040
surreptitiously compiled the entrance statistics

02:13:47.040 --> 02:13:49.840
for a sample of applicants to Georgetown's law school

02:13:49.840 --> 02:13:54.400
and then published the results of his research in the law school student newspaper.

02:13:54.400 --> 02:13:57.920
He revealed that the mean on the law school aptitude test

02:13:57.920 --> 02:14:02.720
differed by a large margin for accepted black and white students.

02:14:02.720 --> 02:14:04.720
Hernstein and Murray dubbed this difference

02:14:04.720 --> 02:14:08.640
the ethnic premium or edge that minority applicants

02:14:08.640 --> 02:14:12.080
are supposedly being afforded in the admissions process

02:14:12.080 --> 02:14:15.440
and go on to detail how they've looked at the college admissions data

02:14:15.440 --> 02:14:21.360
from 26 colleges and found that in the classes entering those in 1991 and 92,

02:14:21.360 --> 02:14:24.080
the average SAT scores of the black students

02:14:24.080 --> 02:14:27.760
were below the average SAT scores of the white students.

02:14:27.760 --> 02:14:29.760
Hernstein and Murray take this as proof

02:14:29.760 --> 02:14:34.080
that black students have an unfair edge in the college admissions process.

02:14:34.080 --> 02:14:38.720
Quote, the summary statement about affirmative action in undergraduate institutions

02:14:38.720 --> 02:14:41.680
is that being either a black or a Latino

02:14:41.680 --> 02:14:44.240
is worth a great deal in the admissions process

02:14:44.240 --> 02:14:48.080
at every undergraduate school for which we have data.

02:14:48.080 --> 02:14:52.720
However, this method of measuring the supposed results of affirmative action

02:14:52.720 --> 02:14:54.720
is entirely incorrect.

02:14:54.720 --> 02:14:57.680
There is a crucial flaw in the logic here

02:14:57.680 --> 02:15:01.600
and it begins with Hernstein and Murray's decision to begin their analysis

02:15:01.600 --> 02:15:05.840
by looking at the college entrance data instead of earlier

02:15:05.840 --> 02:15:09.600
by thinking about the wider pool of college applicants.

02:15:09.600 --> 02:15:14.160
So black people have historically had lower SAT scores than white people.

02:15:14.160 --> 02:15:19.360
Now whether you believe this is due to some fixed genetically originated lower IQ

02:15:19.360 --> 02:15:22.960
or you're sensible and you believe it's down to environmental reasons,

02:15:22.960 --> 02:15:24.240
it is the case.

02:15:24.240 --> 02:15:28.960
So in any random group of students applying to a college in the United States,

02:15:28.960 --> 02:15:33.040
we would expect the scores of the black students to be on average

02:15:33.040 --> 02:15:35.600
lower than the white students if you follow.

02:15:35.600 --> 02:15:39.520
So what happens next is the college takes a look at this group of applicants

02:15:39.520 --> 02:15:43.840
and decides to omit some of them using certain criteria.

02:15:43.840 --> 02:15:46.640
So test scores but usually various other things

02:15:46.640 --> 02:15:49.840
like extracurricular activities and whatever else.

02:15:49.840 --> 02:15:52.320
So all the accepted students get in

02:15:52.320 --> 02:15:56.320
and all the denied students go off to apply somewhere else, right?

02:15:56.320 --> 02:15:58.720
Then Hernstein and Murray come along to the college

02:15:58.720 --> 02:16:01.440
and they notice that the scores of the black students

02:16:01.440 --> 02:16:03.680
are on average below the white students

02:16:03.680 --> 02:16:08.080
and thus start decrying the terrible unfairness of affirmative action.

02:16:08.080 --> 02:16:10.640
But what they've missed here is that this discrepancy

02:16:10.640 --> 02:16:13.920
between the average black and white scores would still exist

02:16:13.920 --> 02:16:19.040
even if the college admissions process only considered test scores and nothing else.

02:16:19.040 --> 02:16:20.640
And let's think about this.

02:16:20.640 --> 02:16:23.920
Imagine an American college in 1991

02:16:23.920 --> 02:16:26.560
with a certain amount of positions to fill

02:16:26.560 --> 02:16:31.040
and they get a larger group of students applying for those positions, right?

02:16:31.040 --> 02:16:34.160
So they have to let some in and not others.

02:16:34.160 --> 02:16:37.760
In that group of applicants there will be a range of test scores

02:16:37.760 --> 02:16:42.720
and the black applicants will have on average lower scores than the white applicants.

02:16:42.720 --> 02:16:46.240
And let's say this college only admits people via test scores

02:16:46.240 --> 02:16:49.200
so if they have 1,000 positions to fill

02:16:49.200 --> 02:16:54.800
they only accept the top 1,000 SAT scores and they send everyone else packing.

02:16:54.800 --> 02:16:58.240
Now in this group of 1,000 successful applicants

02:16:58.240 --> 02:17:00.960
there will still be both black and white people

02:17:00.960 --> 02:17:04.400
but of those black people who scored high enough to get in

02:17:04.400 --> 02:17:08.480
they will be on average towards the lower end of the range.

02:17:08.480 --> 02:17:12.640
Meaning the black group average will still be lower than the white group average

02:17:12.640 --> 02:17:16.000
even though they all scored high enough to get in.

02:17:16.000 --> 02:17:18.320
Even in a world without affirmative action

02:17:18.320 --> 02:17:21.600
and even with a totally racially blind admissions policy

02:17:21.600 --> 02:17:25.680
and accepting Hearnstein and Murray's positions regarding racial IQ scores

02:17:25.680 --> 02:17:31.520
a disparity between black and white SAT scores in college intake groups would still exist.

02:17:31.520 --> 02:17:35.600
The only way we could fairly expect the two averages to be the same

02:17:35.600 --> 02:17:39.680
is if the black and white students in that 1991 applicant pool

02:17:39.680 --> 02:17:42.800
also had on average the same scores.

02:17:42.800 --> 02:17:46.640
And since Hearnstein and Murray have just spent a huge section of their book

02:17:46.640 --> 02:17:49.760
arguing for black people's lower cognitive ability

02:17:49.760 --> 02:17:52.400
I don't know why they'd be expecting that.

02:17:52.400 --> 02:17:55.920
Moving on from affirmative action I'd like to ask a question.

02:17:56.560 --> 02:18:01.040
Can the politics of the bell curve be described as eugenics?

02:18:01.040 --> 02:18:02.960
And I mean yes, right?

02:18:02.960 --> 02:18:06.800
They're arguing for policies with the agenda of changing birth rates

02:18:06.800 --> 02:18:08.800
for particular groups of people.

02:18:08.800 --> 02:18:12.320
They want lower IQ mothers to have fewer children.

02:18:12.320 --> 02:18:16.800
Hearnstein and Murray stop short of openly embracing eugenics however.

02:18:16.800 --> 02:18:21.360
They pull a rhetorical trick by saying they're simply worried about dysgenics.

02:18:21.360 --> 02:18:24.080
Dysgenics being the opposite of eugenics there.

02:18:24.080 --> 02:18:29.120
So we're not necessarily for it but we are anti the opposite of it.

02:18:29.120 --> 02:18:30.240
You know, it's very clever.

02:18:30.240 --> 02:18:36.320
One telling quote here is when Hearnstein and Murray talking about the Nazis say the following

02:18:36.320 --> 02:18:40.560
followed by the terrors of Nazism and its perversion of eugenics

02:18:40.560 --> 02:18:44.000
that effectively wiped the idea from public discourse in the West.

02:18:44.640 --> 02:18:49.760
Now the phrase perversion of eugenics should set off some alarm bells there

02:18:49.760 --> 02:18:53.120
implying apparently that there is a good sort of eugenics

02:18:53.120 --> 02:18:57.520
and the Nazis just did it wrong or took it too far or something.

02:18:57.520 --> 02:19:02.240
Or maybe there was just something uniquely evil about Nazi eugenics

02:19:02.240 --> 02:19:05.920
that wasn't present in the supposedly good eugenics.

02:19:05.920 --> 02:19:06.800
Is that true?

02:19:07.440 --> 02:19:09.280
Well, let's find out.

02:19:09.280 --> 02:19:13.440
The footage you're seeing here is from a movie called Herb Crank.

02:19:13.440 --> 02:19:16.000
In English, the Hereditary Defective.

02:19:16.560 --> 02:19:22.400
This is a 1936 propaganda film produced by the Nazi party's racial policy office.

02:19:22.400 --> 02:19:25.600
It features video shots at German psychiatric hospitals

02:19:25.600 --> 02:19:28.320
of people with various types of disabilities

02:19:28.320 --> 02:19:31.840
interspersed with text informing the audience, among other things,

02:19:31.840 --> 02:19:34.640
of the expense of caring for these people.

02:19:34.640 --> 02:19:40.480
Going on to argue that the prevention of hereditarily sick offspring is a moral duty.

02:19:40.480 --> 02:19:43.840
Now I'm not actually showing the images of the people in the video here

02:19:43.840 --> 02:19:46.800
as they almost certainly did not consent to be in a film

02:19:46.800 --> 02:19:50.480
which was used to propagandize in favor of their sterilization

02:19:50.480 --> 02:19:53.920
and I would feel uncomfortable including that footage in my video.

02:19:54.480 --> 02:19:58.720
Herb Crank is available online though if you prefer to watch it unedited.

02:19:58.720 --> 02:20:00.240
The film ends with the quote,

02:20:00.240 --> 02:20:05.120
the farmer who prevents the overgrowth of the weed promotes the valuable.

02:20:05.760 --> 02:20:09.120
The purpose of this film was obviously to increase public support

02:20:09.120 --> 02:20:12.880
for the involuntary sterilization of people with disabilities,

02:20:12.880 --> 02:20:17.600
a Nazi program that would escalate into outright mass murder just a few years later.

02:20:17.600 --> 02:20:20.480
Adolf Hitler was reportedly a fan of Herb Crank

02:20:20.480 --> 02:20:22.960
and encouraged the production of a sequel titled

02:20:22.960 --> 02:20:26.960
Victims of the Past, The Sin Against Blood and Race

02:20:26.960 --> 02:20:31.040
which was shown in cinemas throughout Nazi Germany in 1937.

02:20:31.760 --> 02:20:34.320
So why am I talking about Herb Crank here?

02:20:34.320 --> 02:20:37.840
Is this simply a slippery slope argument perhaps?

02:20:37.840 --> 02:20:42.160
Look where all this eugenics rubbish leads to the Nazis and the Holocaust.

02:20:43.120 --> 02:20:46.240
Now although I think that would be a fair point to make actually,

02:20:46.880 --> 02:20:52.160
no this particular movie has a much more direct link to what we're talking about today.

02:20:52.160 --> 02:20:54.160
Now something that might come as a shock to you

02:20:54.160 --> 02:20:57.840
and it certainly did to me in the process of researching this video

02:20:57.840 --> 02:21:02.640
is the extent of the international eugenics movement prior to World War II.

02:21:03.280 --> 02:21:06.640
Nazi eugenicists were not operating in a bubble

02:21:06.640 --> 02:21:10.400
and most importantly for us here is that they had a reciprocal relationship

02:21:10.400 --> 02:21:12.080
with American eugenicists.

02:21:12.080 --> 02:21:16.240
You see Herb Crank had another big fan in addition to Hitler.

02:21:16.800 --> 02:21:21.040
So this guy is Harry H. Loughlin, an American eugenicist,

02:21:21.040 --> 02:21:23.520
director of the Eugenics Record Office

02:21:23.520 --> 02:21:27.680
and founding member of the American Eugenics Society.

02:21:27.680 --> 02:21:30.240
He likes eugenics if you didn't pick up on that.

02:21:30.240 --> 02:21:34.080
Now in 1922 Harry Loughlin published a book titled

02:21:34.080 --> 02:21:36.960
Eugenical Sterilization in the United States

02:21:36.960 --> 02:21:41.840
which included a chapter titled Model Eugenical Sterilization Law.

02:21:41.840 --> 02:21:43.360
This model law begins

02:21:43.360 --> 02:21:49.600
an act to prevent the procreation of persons socially inadequate from defective inheritance

02:21:49.600 --> 02:21:53.440
by authorizing and providing for the eugenical sterilization

02:21:53.440 --> 02:21:58.400
of certain potential parents carrying degenerate hereditary qualities.

02:21:58.400 --> 02:22:01.520
This law designates a socially inadequate person

02:22:01.520 --> 02:22:06.400
as someone who fails chronically in comparison with normal persons

02:22:06.400 --> 02:22:08.560
to maintain himself or herself

02:22:08.560 --> 02:22:12.560
as a useful member of the organized social life of the state.

02:22:12.560 --> 02:22:16.000
These socially inadequate people were not just the ill

02:22:16.000 --> 02:22:21.200
but also for example the criminalistic, the inebriate and the dependent

02:22:21.200 --> 02:22:27.360
including orphans, ne'er-do-wells, the homeless, tramps and paupers.

02:22:27.360 --> 02:22:30.800
18 US states passed laws based upon Loughlin's model

02:22:30.800 --> 02:22:34.320
and between them sterilized tens of thousands of people.

02:22:34.320 --> 02:22:40.560
And in 1933 somewhere else passed a law which was based upon Loughlin's model.

02:22:40.560 --> 02:22:44.480
The law for the prevention of hereditarily diseased offspring

02:22:44.480 --> 02:22:48.320
which actually was slightly more moderate than what the model law proposed

02:22:48.320 --> 02:22:49.600
if you can believe it.

02:22:49.600 --> 02:22:52.320
This was of course Nazi Germany.

02:22:52.320 --> 02:22:56.960
Loughlin was later awarded an honorary degree by the University of Heidelberg

02:22:56.960 --> 02:22:59.120
for his work on behalf of the quote,

02:22:59.120 --> 02:23:01.360
science of racial cleansing.

02:23:01.360 --> 02:23:04.640
Loughlin was also an open Nazi party supporter

02:23:04.640 --> 02:23:08.080
writing enthusiastically about Nazi Germany's eugenics laws

02:23:08.080 --> 02:23:11.200
in a publication titled Eugenic News.

02:23:11.760 --> 02:23:14.080
And why shouldn't he be excited about them?

02:23:14.080 --> 02:23:15.680
I mean, he wrote them.

